news.title: MHADA reduces price by 10-25% on 370 surplus tenements in Mumbai board lottery
news.para: Atul Save, housing minister, Maharashtra while giving details about the reductions informed that a 25% cut for the economically weaker section (EWS), 20% for the low-income group (LIG), 15% for the middle-income group (MIG), and 10% for the high-income group (HIG) is being extended.

news.title: Germany: Aroundtown's loss narrows to $481.5 million in Q2 2024
news.para: Aroundtown, one of the largest listed landlords in the country, said its second-quarter loss narrowed to 432 million euros ($481.5 million) from 1.27 billion a year earlier.

news.title: Can't slap stamp duty on sale agreement when deed is executed: Karnataka HC
news.para: The petitioners, the plaintiffs in the partition suit, claimed that there is already a sale deed and they produced the agreement of sale only as evidence in support of their claim in that particular partition suit to demonstrate that they are in possession.

news.title: Union cabinet approves 12 new industrial cities with an outlay of Rs 28,602 crore
news.para: These industrial areas will be located in Khurpia in Uttrakhand, Rajpura-Patiala in Punjab, Dighi in Maharashtra, Palakkad in Kerala, Agra and Prayagraj in UP, Gaya in Bihar, Zaheerabad in Telangana, Orvakal and Kopparthy in AP, and Jodhpur-Pali in Rajasthan.

news.title: Circle rates of key Ayodhya locations likely to see 200% rise
news.para: The rates here were revised last in 2017. The final rate list that would offer clarity to the interested buyers on the quantum of the hike would be available publicly on Wednesday or Thursday.

news.title: Sweden's SBB posts $343.79 million loss in Q2 2024
news.para: The landlord, which racked up debt buying properties such as schools and hospitals, reported an April-June loss before tax of 3.5 billion Swedish crowns ($343.79 million), smaller than a revised 10 billion crown loss a year earlier.

news.title: Office leasing in top eight cities expected to cross 80 million sq ft in 2024: Report
news.para: Bengaluru and Mumbai saw the highest growth of 132% and 71% on a year-on-year basis, followed by Hyderabad and Kolkata.

news.title: BMC can levy water tax even if premises lie unused: Bombay HC
news.para: The Bombay High Court permits BMC to levy water tax and water benefit tax on property tax bills irrespective of water consumption. Yet, if water charges for actual consumption are paid, these taxes cannot be imposed additionally. The ruling originates from a case filed in 2005 involving Mars Enterprises over a south Mumbai property.

news.title: NBCC to consider bonus issue, shares surge 8% on August 28
news.para: Shares of central PSU NBCC climbed 8% to Rs 192.40 on BSE following the company's announcement to consider issuing bonus shares. The meeting is scheduled for August 31, 2024. NBCC, previously distributing bonus shares in February 2017, often rewards its shareholders with dividend payouts.

news.title: Australia's BGC sues Fletcher Building over leaky pipes dispute
news.para: The homes, 90% of which were built by BGC and partner Delstrat and outfitted with plumbing pipes made by Fletcher's unit, suffered leaks between mid-2017 and mid-2022.

news.title: Home prices in Hong Kong drop 1.9% in July 2024
news.para: The prices have tumbled 25.4% from their 2021 peak, hitting the lowest since September 2016, hurt by higher mortgage rates, an outflow of talent and a weak market outlook.

news.title: Residents from four gram panchayats demand inclusion in Mysuru civic body limits
news.para: The residents of these local bodies located on the outskirts of Mysuru have been demanding that the state govt to include their areas by forming a Greater Mysuru City Corporation. Currently, MCC has spread over 65 wards.

news.title: Tamil Nadu CM launches six CMDA projects in north Chennai
news.para: Chief minister M K Stalin laid the foundation for the project and five others under the North Chennai Development Scheme of CMDA, valued at 115.58 crore. He also inaugurated completed projects worth 5.22 crore in other departments.

news.title: Seven Indian cities see 45% hike in average house prices in five years: Anarock
news.para: Hyderabad recorded the highest jump of 64% between 2019 and H1 2024, followed by Bengaluru with a 57% increase. The lowest price growth of 25% was seen in Kolkata. NCR and MMR both witnessed a 48% price appreciation each in this period.

news.title: Awfis join hands with Nyati Group to manage three lakh sq ft workspace in Pune
news.para: Awfis Space Solutions will operate a total of 1,67,206 sq ft built up flexible workspaces at Nyati Empress in Viman Nagar and Nyati Enthral in Kharadi, Pune.

news.title: Gautam Buddh Nagar to e-auction industrial plots up to 8,000 sq meter
news.para: On July 6 last year, UP industrial development commissioner Manoj Kumar Singh issued a letter directing the authorities to abolish the e-auction process and reinstate the previous objective criteria method, effective before April 2022

news.title: Karnataka government to implement ‘anywhere registration' on September 2
news.para: This concept, originally introduced in Bengaluru in 2011, permitted property registrations at any sub-registrar office within the Gandhinagar, Basavanagudi, Jayanagar, Shivajinagar, and Rajajinagar district registration offices.

news.title: Kangana Ranaut buys office property in Mumbai’s Andheri west
news.para: Kangana Ranaut has paid stamp duty of over Rs 9.37 lakh for the registration of the deal that took place on August 23, showed the documents accessed through realty data analytics firm Propstack.

news.title: Elan Group awards over Rs 500 crore construction contract to Leighton Asia
news.para: The mall will span approximately nine acres with a total built-up area of about 2.5 million sq ft. The construction is expected to begin in November 2024 and is designed by BENOY, an architectural firm.
